22/07/2004
WASHINGTON, United States -- Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and US President George W. Bush discussed a number of bilateral and international issues during a meeting Wednesday (21 July) at the White House.
The talks focused on US-Romanian relations and the situations in Iraq and Afghanistan, where Romania has contributed troops to the international peacekeeping missions.
Bush praised Romania's support for the rebuilding and democratisation process in Iraq.
He also urged the continuation of economic reforms in Romania, stressing that bilateral economic co-operation would be boosted as market conditions there improve.
Afterwards, Nastase said he had reiterated an offer to house relocated US military bases in Romania.
(Rompres - 22/07/04;
Reuters - 21/07/04)
